# Regime Playbook — Single Source of Truth

This rule exists because "regime" and "layer" are overloaded terms in this codebase. Every other regime rule defers to the definitions here.

---

## Vocabulary — Three Separate Systems

| Term | Values | File | Purpose |
|---|---|---|---|
| **L1 Execution Regime** | `STRONG_UPTREND` `CHOPPY` `MIXED` `STRONG_DOWNTREND` `UNFAVORABLE` | `logs/regime_context.json` | Controls which strategies may *enter* positions today |
| **L2 Macro Band** | `RISK_ON` `NEUTRAL` `TIGHTENING` `DEFENSIVE` | `logs/regime_state.json` | Scales individual position *sizes* via a multiplier |
| **Risk Escalation Tiers** | Tier 1 (Kill Switch) / Tier 2 (Drawdown) / Tier 3 (Assignment) | `kill_switch.json` `drawdown_breaker_state.json` | Hard halts — orthogonal to both regime systems above |

> Never call the risk tiers "Layer 1/2/3" — that collides with L1/L2 regime terminology. See `risk-monitoring.mdc`.

