## L2 Macro Band — Position Size Multipliers

Read from `logs/regime_state.json → parameters.sizeMultiplier`. Applied *on top of* L1 allocation by `get_macro_size_multiplier()` in `regime_detector.py`.

| L2 Band | Size Multiplier | Effect |
|---|---|---|
| `RISK_ON` | 1.00 | Full position sizes |
| `NEUTRAL` | 0.75 | 25% size reduction |
| `TIGHTENING` | 0.50 | Half size |
| `DEFENSIVE` | 0.25 | Quarter size |

### Combined L1 + L2 example

CHOPPY (L1) + TIGHTENING (L2):
- Long book target: 85% of NLV
- Each individual long position sized at 50% of normal
- Net effect: can hold many positions, but each is smaller than usual

UNFAVORABLE (L1) + any L2:
- No new entries regardless of L2 multiplier
- L2 multiplier is irrelevant when entry is blocked

