## Adaptive Override

`adaptive_config.json` can override `_DEFAULT_ALLOCATIONS` via `_load_adaptive_allocations()`. When the adaptive system is active, the allocation percentages above may differ from the defaults. The logic in `regime_detector.py → calculate_portfolio_allocation()` always checks adaptive config first. Verify live values:

```bash
python -c "from regime_detector import calculate_portfolio_allocation; print(calculate_portfolio_allocation('CHOPPY'))"
```

